2026-07-01 | Maximum Subarray Sum with One Deletion

	Question
Return the maximum possible subarray sum after deleting at most one element.
	Key Insight
This is an extension of Kadane's Algorithm.
For every index, maintain two values:
		noDelete
	= Maximum subarray sum ending at current index without deleting any element.
		oneDelete
	= Maximum subarray sum ending at current index after deleting exactly one element.
	Transition
	Case 1: No deletion used
	Either:
		Start a new subarray
	or
		Extend the previous one.
		noDelete =
		max(arr[i],
		    noDelete + arr[i])
	Case 2: One deletion used
	Two possibilities:
	•	Delete current element
			oneDelete = previous noDelete
	•	Deletion already used earlier
			Extend current element
			oneDelete + arr[i]
	So,
		oneDelete =
		max(previous noDelete,
		    previous oneDelete + arr[i])
	The answer is the maximum value among all states.
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
			noDelete = arr[0]
			oneDelete = 0
2.	Traverse the array.
3.	Update the two DP states.
4.	Track the maximum answer.
5.	Return the answer.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumSubarray(vector<int>& arr) {
        int noDelete = arr[0];
        int oneDelete = 0;
        int ans = arr[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < arr.size(); i++) {
            int prevNoDelete = noDelete;
            noDelete = max(arr[i], noDelete + arr[i]);
            oneDelete = max(prevNoDelete,
                            oneDelete + arr[i]);
            ans = max(ans, max(noDelete, oneDelete));
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Example
	Input:
		arr = [1,-2,0,3]
	Without deletion:
		Maximum sum = 3
	Delete:
		-2
	Subarray becomes:
		[1,0,3]
	Sum:
		4
	Output:
		4
	Key Insight
	At every position, there are only two meaningful states:
	- Continue without using any deletion.
	- Continue after having used exactly one deletion (either earlier or by deleting the current element).
	Maintaining these two states while scanning the array gives the optimal solution in **O(n)** time and **O(1)** extra space.
